@model TheFishingSpot.Web.Models.UserProfileViewModel
<h3>Add a fish</h3>
@using (Html.BeginForm("Add", "News", FormMethod.Post, new { @class = "form-horizontal", role = "form" }))
{
    @Html.AntiForgeryToken()
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Name, new { @class = "col-md-2 control-label" })
        <div class="col-md-10">
            @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Name, new { @class = "form-control" })
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Type, new { @class = "col-md-2 control-label" })
        <div class="col-md-10">
            @Html.EnumDropDownListFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Type, new { @class = "form-control" })
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Weight, new { @class = "col-md-2 control-label" })
        <div class="col-md-10">
            @Html.EditorFor(m => m.FishInputModel.Weight)
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.FishInputModel.AdditionalInfo, new { @class = "col-md-2 control-label" })
        <div class="col-md-10">
            @Html.EditorFor(m => m.FishInputModel.AdditionalInfo)
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        <div class="col-md-offset-2 col-md-10">
            <input type="submit" class="btn btn-default" value="Add" />
        </div>
    </div>
}
